In this folder third-party components will be downloaded. They are usually
needed to support various platforms. To download these components, run the
./download-3rdparty-components.sh script.

These are the libs that are downloaded by the script:

1. EV3-API
   License: GNU GPLv2/BSD License
   Description: Needed for legoev3 platform to work, a really nice C wrapper
   to LEGO's proprietary EV3 API
   Code URL: https://github.com/c4ev3/EV3-API
   GPLv2 URL: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.ru.html
   BSD URL: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_licenses

2. pigpio
   License: Public Domain License
   Description: Needed for pigpio_rpi platform to work
   Code URL: http://abyz.me.uk/rpi/pigpio

3. StandardCplusplus
   License: GNU LGPLv2.1
   Description: Needed for arduinoavr platform to work, a port of uclibc++
   to Arduino.
   Code URL: https://github.com/maniacbug/StandardCplusplus

4. ArduinoCore-avr Slim Edition
   License: GNU LGPLv2.1
   Description: Needed for arduinoavr platform to work ONLY IF ARDUINO IDE
   IS NOT INSTALLED. And yes, this is the Arduino.h library, except all
   unnecessary stuff was removed.
   Code URL: https://github.com/arduino/ArduinoCore-avr